WEBVTT

1
00:02:25.030 --> 00:02:27.830
<i>- Si­. Bueno.
- Family is everything.</i>

2
00:02:27.930 --> 00:02:29.730
<i>No?</i>

3
00:02:29.830 --> 00:02:33.230
<i>Now. do you love your son?</i>

4
00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:37.970
Si­.

5
00:02:44.850 --> 00:02:49.440
<i>Now... do you understand?</i>

6
00:02:49.550 --> 00:02:53.920
<i>You have a $10 million insurance policy.
I know that.</i>

7
00:05:03.420 --> 00:05:05.550
Georgina!

8
00:05:05.650 --> 00:05:08.920
Obey me. I will love you.
Come on.

9
00:05:09.020 --> 00:05:10.790
That's how it works. huh?

10
00:05:10.890 --> 00:05:14.060
<i>- Simple.
- That's right.</i>

11
00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:16.060
Mwah.

12
00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:23.500
She got a sister?

13
00:05:23.610 --> 00:05:26.800
How's business?

14
00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:29.810
The Japanese are here in a big way.

15
00:05:31.250 --> 00:05:33.740
Cheap labor. factory space.

16
00:05:33.850 --> 00:05:37.810
But they feel a lot safer living
over the border in El Paso.

17
00:05:37.920 --> 00:05:40.980
I ferry them back and forth.
They think I'm John Wayne.

18
00:05:41.090 --> 00:05:42.990
- Ah.
- Come on.

19
00:05:47.460 --> 00:05:50.690
- I live like a king down here.
- Yes. you do.

20
00:05:54.440 --> 00:05:57.600
- You been workin'?
- Yeah. No.

21
00:05:57.710 --> 00:05:59.770
Nah. Been movin' around.
you know.

22
00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:03.940
Colombia. couple of places I can't name.
Nothing catches my fancy.

23
00:06:05.810 --> 00:06:08.780
Oh.

24
00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:11.440
You think God will forgive us
for what we've done?

25
00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:14.110
- No.
- You don't?

26
00:06:14.220 --> 00:06:18.390
Me either.

27
00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:23.300
- How long you staying?
- I don't know. I just... you know.

28
00:06:23.400 --> 00:06:27.360
I wanted to see you. Ray.
see how you're doin'.

29
00:06:27.470 --> 00:06:29.990
You know. I came by on impulse.

30
00:06:30.110 --> 00:06:33.670
Well. I could do with some impulse.

31
00:06:43.790 --> 00:06:46.810
What happened?

32
00:06:46.920 --> 00:06:49.120
Family paid the ransom...

33
00:06:49.220 --> 00:06:53.220
then they sent the kid home
after a couple of days...

34
00:06:53.330 --> 00:06:55.490
minus an ear. of course.

35
00:06:55.600 --> 00:06:59.230
Now every mother in Mexico City with a little
bit of money wants bigger and better bodyguards...

36
00:06:59.330 --> 00:07:01.300
my own wife included.

37
00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:04.700
I hate to break it to you.
but she's right. She's right.

38
00:07:06.410 --> 00:07:10.670
Look. Sammy. all my clients have. uh.
kidnap and ransom insurance.

39
00:07:10.780 --> 00:07:14.010
I have a policy. A.I.G.
My dad gave it to me.

40
00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:17.380
Yeah. I know.
I got it for your dad.

41
00:07:17.490 --> 00:07:20.420
<i>But what are you gonna do in 60 days
when you can't renew it?</i>

42
00:07:20.520 --> 00:07:24.790
- You can't because you don't have a bodyguard.
- I had to let Emilio go.

43
00:07:24.890 --> 00:07:28.520
You gotta please Lisa.
I mean. hey. ass like that's hard to find.

44
00:07:30.970 --> 00:07:35.230
Look. a bodyguard's
like anything else.

45
00:07:35.340 --> 00:07:38.600
You get what you pay for. okay?

46
00:07:38.710 --> 00:07:41.700
You could do this.
You get one that's got a decent resume.

47
00:07:41.810 --> 00:07:44.140
We're not looking for
goddamn Superman here. right?

48
00:07:44.250 --> 00:07:46.980
Get someone cheap
till you renew the policy...

49
00:07:47.080 --> 00:07:50.450
and then. uh...
then fire the prick for whatever.

50
00:07:50.550 --> 00:07:52.610
Incompetence.

51
00:07:52.720 --> 00:07:57.120
All kidding aside. the most important thing
is that your daughter goes back to school...

52
00:07:57.230 --> 00:08:00.200
and that your wife gets to save face.

53
00:08:00.300 --> 00:08:05.100
This way. you won't be the only
unprotected family in the neighborhood.

54
00:08:17.710 --> 00:08:20.910
<i>That's right. A bodyguard.
Your Spanish is good enough.</i>

55
00:08:21.020 --> 00:08:24.420
- You're crazy.
- You even look the part.

56
00:08:24.520 --> 00:08:26.990
In my state.
I couldn't guard a corpse.

57
00:08:27.090 --> 00:08:29.890
<i>It's rich guys flashing their cash.
It's all for show.</i>

58
00:08:29.990 --> 00:08:35.120
<i>- Nothing's gonna happen. - Yeah? You
think they'd hire a drunk. a has-been?</i>

59
00:08:36.800 --> 00:08:40.100
You have to keep it under control.

60
00:08:40.200 --> 00:08:44.970
What if there was. you know. say.
a kidnapping attempt? What do I do then?

61
00:08:45.070 --> 00:08:49.100
<i>You do your best. They're not gonna be
paying you enough to perform miracles.</i>

62
00:08:49.210 --> 00:08:51.810
<i>- I don't know.
- It's not exactly a scam. Crease.</i>

63
00:08:51.910 --> 00:08:56.150
- Even at half speed. you're pretty damn good.
- Yeah.

64
00:08:56.250 --> 00:08:58.450
Bodyguard's gotta be close
to people though.

65
00:08:58.550 --> 00:09:01.390
He gotta talk all the time.
and I'm no good at that.

66
00:09:01.490 --> 00:09:05.020
You'll be the silent type.
People are gonna appreciate that.

67
00:09:11.970 --> 00:09:14.830
Bodyguard. So who's the guy?

68
00:09:14.940 --> 00:09:17.840
Samuel Ramos. He's a young guy.

69
00:09:17.940 --> 00:09:20.740
<i>He owns one of the plants in Juárez.</i>

70
00:09:20.840 --> 00:09:22.780
<i>Yeah?</i>

71
00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:25.680
The Jap car industry is in the toilet.

72
00:09:25.780 --> 00:09:28.720
He's trying to persuade Ford
to partner with him.

73
00:09:28.820 --> 00:09:32.690
I think he's in trouble.
His family lives in Mexico City.

74
00:09:32.790 --> 00:09:35.310
He asked me if I knew
anybody he could trust.

75
00:09:36.890 --> 00:09:39.880
- And you thought of me.
- Yeah.

76
00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:43.400
Take a job. Crease.
Breathe some air.

77
00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:45.860
<i>Then decide if you want
to stick around or not.</i>

78
00:09:45.970 --> 00:09:50.060
<i>Besides. I'm glad to see you.
I got nobody to talk to down here.</i>

79
00:09:57.550 --> 00:10:00.450
Listen. my wife wants someone
presentable and polite.

80
00:10:02.820 --> 00:10:06.350
You'll be the fifth candidate
she sees this week.

81
00:10:06.460 --> 00:10:08.180
Your resume's quite impressive.

82
00:10:08.290 --> 00:10:12.750
<i>Sixteen years of military experience.
extensive counterterrorism work.</i>

83
00:10:12.860 --> 00:10:16.420
I'm surprised anybody could afford you.
What's the catch?

84
00:10:16.530 --> 00:10:18.800
I drink.

85
00:10:18.900 --> 00:10:20.890
How does that affect you?

86
00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:23.470
Well...

87
00:10:23.570 --> 00:10:25.700
coordination. reaction time.

88
00:10:25.810 --> 00:10:29.570
If top professionals try to kidnap
your daughter. I'll do the best I can...

89
00:10:29.680 --> 00:10:32.700
but the service will be
on par with the pay.

90
00:10:33.850 --> 00:10:35.870
What if amateurs tried?

91
00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:39.110
I'd probably kill 'em.
Is that likely?

92
00:10:39.220 --> 00:10:41.190
No.

93
00:10:41.290 --> 00:10:44.050
No one is to know about your drinking.
That includes my wife.

94
00:11:10.950 --> 00:11:13.720
<i>Lisa!</i>

95
00:11:15.920 --> 00:11:17.820
Lisa!

96
00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:31.940
My wife. Lisa.
And this is John Creasy.

97
00:11:38.980 --> 00:11:41.210
- You're an American.
- So are you.

98
00:11:43.250 --> 00:11:45.050
It's all in there.

99
00:11:48.090 --> 00:11:50.020
Would you like a drink?

100
00:11:50.130 --> 00:11:52.860
Yes. uh. Jack and water'd be good.

101
00:11:54.430 --> 00:11:57.960
<i>- Have you done much of this kind of work before?
- No. ma'am.</i>

102
00:11:58.070 --> 00:12:01.830
But he has a lot of experience
in related fields.

103
00:12:04.340 --> 00:12:07.040
- You have a family. Mr. Creasy?
- No.

104
00:12:07.140 --> 00:12:09.340
Pita.

105
00:12:09.440 --> 00:12:11.410
<i>Pita.</i>

106
00:12:12.750 --> 00:12:14.840
<i>- Thank you.
- Yes. Mom?</i>

107
00:12:14.950 --> 00:12:16.850
Honey. this is. uh. Mr. Creasy.

108
00:12:22.020 --> 00:12:24.490
In English. honey.

109
00:12:24.590 --> 00:12:27.220
Um. do you wanna show
Mr. Creasy to his room?

110
00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:31.030
- This way. Mr. Creasy.
- Okay.

111
00:12:39.040 --> 00:12:41.440
Thank you.

112
00:12:48.380 --> 00:12:51.180
Just like that?

113
00:12:51.290 --> 00:12:53.690
I think it's nice...

114
00:12:53.790 --> 00:12:56.260
that he's an American.

115
00:12:56.360 --> 00:13:00.560
I think it's terrific. You sure?

116
00:13:03.230 --> 00:13:05.530
Thank you.

117
00:13:05.630 --> 00:13:08.260
Thank you.

118
00:13:08.370 --> 00:13:10.840
I feel better now.

119
00:13:12.740 --> 00:13:15.640
<i>- Hola. Bruno!
- Buenas tardes!</i>

120
00:13:15.740 --> 00:13:18.040
That's Bruno. the gardener.

121
00:13:18.150 --> 00:13:20.210
And. um. that's Maria. the cook.

122
00:13:20.320 --> 00:13:23.110
<i>- Hola. Maria!
- Hola. Pita.</i>

123
00:13:25.390 --> 00:13:29.410
We fixed the room up two weeks ago.
It's nicer than before.

124
00:13:32.590 --> 00:13:36.430
<i>You've got a TV and C.D. Player.
What kind of music do you like. Mr. Creasy?</i>

125
00:13:36.530 --> 00:13:38.900
I don't know.

126
00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:41.490
- You don't know?
- I don't know.

127
00:13:41.600 --> 00:13:44.770
That's Bird.

128
00:13:44.870 --> 00:13:47.740
Emilio forgot to take him
when he left.

129
00:13:48.910 --> 00:13:51.240
Emilio was my last bodyguard.

130
00:13:53.250 --> 00:13:57.480
Have you protected a lot of children
before. Mr. Creasy?

131
00:13:57.590 --> 00:14:00.350
Creasy. You can call me Creasy.
And no. you're the first.

132
00:14:00.460 --> 00:14:02.360
Creasy.

133
00:14:02.460 --> 00:14:04.390
Bye. Creasy.

134
00:14:04.490 --> 00:14:07.150
So long.

135
00:14:08.260 --> 00:14:09.990
Bye. Bird.

136
00:14:14.670 --> 00:14:17.000
Ow.

137
00:14:19.980 --> 00:14:23.470
- School tomorrow. peeps.
- Does that mean we can get a dog?

138
00:14:24.880 --> 00:14:27.350
<i>Dad promised me one
when I went back to school.</i>

139
00:14:27.450 --> 00:14:29.140
Yeah. we'll see.

140
00:14:29.250 --> 00:14:33.050
If you get a dog.
will you give up your bear?

141
00:14:33.150 --> 00:14:36.490
You're getting too old for him.

142
00:14:36.590 --> 00:14:39.990
<i>- How'd you like Mr. Creasy?
- Creasy.</i>

143
00:14:40.100 --> 00:14:42.460
He said to call him just Creasy.

144
00:14:42.560 --> 00:14:45.030
- Uh-huh.
- That isn't disrespectful. is it?

145
00:14:45.130 --> 00:14:47.430
No. not if he asked you.

146
00:14:47.540 --> 00:14:50.370
Here. There you go.

147
00:14:58.210 --> 00:15:02.010
- He's like a bear too.
- Yeah?

148
00:15:02.120 --> 00:15:04.420
A big. sad bear.

149
00:15:06.050 --> 00:15:09.680
- Is he sad?
- I think. Or something.

150
00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:15.400
- Good night. honey.
- Night.

151
00:15:18.830 --> 00:15:22.100
- Oh. can you get me some floss in the morning?
- Floss?

152
00:15:22.200 --> 00:15:25.730
- Yeah. the strawberry kind.
- Oh. sure.

153
00:15:28.080 --> 00:15:30.100
Good night. Bear.

154
00:15:31.210 --> 00:15:33.180
Creasy Bear.

155
00:16:06.720 --> 00:16:09.050
What's that one for?

156
00:16:09.150 --> 00:16:11.050
<i>La Virgin de Guadalupe.</i>

157
00:16:11.150 --> 00:16:15.560
Business. For Toyota. for Ford.

158
00:16:15.660 --> 00:16:18.290
If one dies. maybe she can
resurrect the other one.

159
00:16:18.390 --> 00:16:20.950
I don't know.

160
00:16:21.060 --> 00:16:24.000
She likes him.

161
00:16:25.700 --> 00:16:28.900
- What are you talking about?
- Creasy.

162
00:16:30.440 --> 00:16:33.100
Pita likes him.

163
00:16:33.210 --> 00:16:35.110
Pita loves school.

164
00:16:35.210 --> 00:16:40.410
<i>Pita would love Count Dracula
if he took her back there. honey.</i>

165
00:16:40.520 --> 00:16:42.480
Okay?

166
00:16:44.950 --> 00:16:47.820
<i>- Hey. Are you okay?
- I don't know.</i>

167
00:16:47.920 --> 00:16:52.020
Okay?

168
00:16:52.130 --> 00:16:54.560
I don't know. Lisa.

169
00:16:54.660 --> 00:16:56.630
I'm trying.

170
00:17:52.820 --> 00:17:54.790
Come on. Bird.

171
00:17:54.890 --> 00:17:58.260
That's right.
That's right. Come on.

172
00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:01.520
All right. Home to Emilio.

173
00:18:01.630 --> 00:18:04.500
You're home free. baby.

174
00:18:24.620 --> 00:18:27.380
- Where are you from. Creasy?
- The U.S.

175
00:18:27.490 --> 00:18:30.420
<i>- I know. but which state?
- No state in particular.</i>

176
00:18:30.520 --> 00:18:32.520
You can drive and talk
at the same time.

177
00:18:32.630 --> 00:18:35.090
No. I can't. Pita. so. please.
let me just do my job.

178
00:18:38.400 --> 00:18:41.270
Are you going to stay?

179
00:18:41.370 --> 00:18:43.270
My last bodyguard left.

180
00:18:43.370 --> 00:18:46.240
Somebody gave him
more money than we could.

181
00:18:46.340 --> 00:18:50.300
I guess that makes me
a bargain then. huh?

182
00:18:50.410 --> 00:18:54.810
Being black... is that a positive or negative
for a bodyguard in Mexico?

183
00:18:54.920 --> 00:18:56.820
Time will tell.

184
00:19:00.350 --> 00:19:04.590
There were 24 kidnappings
in Mexico City in the last six days.

185
00:19:04.690 --> 00:19:06.590
- Four a day.
- Yeah?

186
00:19:06.690 --> 00:19:09.160
- Twenty-four? - Twenty-four. What
do you think about that. Creasy?

187
00:19:09.260 --> 00:19:12.930
- I think that you know entirely more than you should.
- Well. thank you.

188
00:19:36.060 --> 00:19:38.680
<i>Hola. Miguel.</i>

189
00:19:41.230 --> 00:19:43.090
- See you later.
- You have to sign.

190
00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:47.500
- What?
- You have to sign in. show them your I.D.

191
00:19:47.600 --> 00:19:51.040
<i>Buenos di­as. Come on.</i>

192
00:19:52.210 --> 00:19:54.110
Right there.

193
00:19:54.210 --> 00:19:56.840
<i>- Hola. Manuel.
- Hola. Pita.</i>

194
00:20:07.620 --> 00:20:09.520
<i>- Hola. Pita!
- Hola!</i>

195
00:20:09.620 --> 00:20:13.820
Pita! It's so good to have you back.

196
00:20:13.930 --> 00:20:16.830
Sister Anna. this is
my new bodyguard. Creasy.

197
00:20:16.930 --> 00:20:20.060
Sister Anna. the headmistress.

198
00:20:20.170 --> 00:20:22.190
<i>Señor Creasy.</i>

199
00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:24.200
Hurry. Class is about to begin.

200
00:20:24.300 --> 00:20:26.640
- Go. go.
- Bye. Creasy.

201
00:20:26.740 --> 00:20:29.230
<i>- Madre.
- You must look after our Pita.</i>

202
00:20:29.340 --> 00:20:31.540
It is not good that she's late today.

203
00:20:31.650 --> 00:20:36.210
I'm very sorry. I. uh... I'll have to get
used to the rules. It won't happen again.

204
00:20:36.320 --> 00:20:39.880
No offense. but I regret
that your profession needs to exist.

205
00:20:39.990 --> 00:20:43.120
<i>So do I. Madre. So do I.</i>

206
00:20:43.220 --> 00:20:47.180
Do you ever see the hand of God
in what you do?

207
00:20:48.800 --> 00:20:50.920
No. not for a long time.

208
00:20:51.030 --> 00:20:54.400
The Bible says.
"Be not overcome of evil. but overcome... "

209
00:20:54.500 --> 00:20:57.940
"Overcome evil with good. "

210
00:21:04.080 --> 00:21:06.880
<i>I'm the sheep that got lost. Madre.</i>

211
00:22:10.280 --> 00:22:13.340
When you were a kid. Creasy.
did you like school?

212
00:22:14.920 --> 00:22:17.110
- I don't remember.
- You don't remember?

213
00:22:17.220 --> 00:22:21.120
No. I don't remember.
It. uh... Nah. I didn't like it.

214
00:22:21.220 --> 00:22:23.280
Why not?

215
00:22:23.390 --> 00:22:25.950
Because it wasn't a school like yours.

216
00:22:26.060 --> 00:22:28.030
There was no. uh... no Sister Anna.

217
00:22:30.930 --> 00:22:33.060
Were you unhappy?

218
00:22:35.270 --> 00:22:38.670
Being unhappy. Pita. that's a state of mind.
I really don't remember.

219
00:22:48.120 --> 00:22:50.210
What happened to your hand?

220
00:22:51.750 --> 00:22:53.650
- It's a birth defect.
- No. it's not.

221
00:22:53.750 --> 00:22:58.020
Look. no more questions. okay?

222
00:22:58.130 --> 00:23:00.490
- It really wasn't a question.
- It sounded like a question.

223
00:23:00.590 --> 00:23:03.190
<i>Look. I got a job to do. Hey!</i>

224
00:23:03.300 --> 00:23:05.530
<i>No. Gracias. Gracias. No. No.</i>

225
00:23:05.630 --> 00:23:08.570
Listen to me.
I'm being paid to protect you. okay?

226
00:23:08.670 --> 00:23:11.640
No. no. no. I'm being paid
to be your bodyguard.

227
00:23:11.740 --> 00:23:14.830
<i>Look at me.
I'm not being paid to be your friend.</i>

228
00:23:14.940 --> 00:23:18.500
<i>I'm being paid to protect you.
so no more questions. That's it. Period.</i>

229
00:23:22.320 --> 00:23:25.010
<i>- You hear me?
- Yes.</i>

230
00:23:25.120 --> 00:23:28.550
- And no crying.
- I'm not crying.

231
00:23:28.660 --> 00:23:31.720
Well. don't start.

232
00:23:31.830 --> 00:23:34.260
You gotta understand. this is a job.

233
00:23:34.360 --> 00:23:37.160
In order for me to do...

234
00:23:37.260 --> 00:23:39.200
In order for... Wait a minute.

235
00:24:28.850 --> 00:24:30.820
Yeah. come in.

236
00:24:36.420 --> 00:24:38.580
Mr. Creasy.

237
00:24:38.690 --> 00:24:41.490
I just wanted to make sure
you have everything you need.

238
00:24:41.600 --> 00:24:43.560
I'm fine. thanks.

239
00:24:45.670 --> 00:24:49.000
Is the food all right?
'Cause. uh. Maria told me you didn't eat.

240
