<i>Si­.</i>

1023
02:04:10.190 --> 02:04:12.590
<i>Si­.</i>

1024
02:04:12.690 --> 02:04:14.630
Huh?

1025
02:05:11.480 --> 02:05:13.450
<i>Momento.</i>

1026
02:05:43.120 --> 02:05:45.050
<i>Hola. Daniel.</i>

1027
02:05:45.150 --> 02:05:47.020
Señor Creasy.

1028
02:05:47.120 --> 02:05:50.490
Yeah. Yeah. I got your family here.

1029
02:05:50.590 --> 02:05:53.150
<i>Your brother doesn't look too good.</i>

1030
02:05:53.260 --> 02:05:56.520
<i>Yeah. Reina. she's what.
about eight months?</i>

1031
02:05:56.630 --> 02:06:00.690
<i>Huh? You wanna negotiate?</i>

1032
02:06:04.600 --> 02:06:08.270
The most important thing
in life is family.

1033
02:06:08.370 --> 02:06:10.570
<i>Do you agree?</i>

1034
02:06:11.780 --> 02:06:13.680
I agree.

1035
02:06:15.480 --> 02:06:17.950
And there you are.
You have my family.

1036
02:06:18.050 --> 02:06:20.920
Well. most of my family.

1037
02:06:21.020 --> 02:06:25.180
<i>My wife and I are separated.
You know how that is.</i>

1038
02:06:25.290 --> 02:06:29.060
Now. tell me seriously.
h- how much do you want?

1039
02:06:29.160 --> 02:06:30.920
Ah.

1040
02:06:33.470 --> 02:06:35.960
Your brother wants to speak to you.
Yeah. hold on.

1041
02:06:47.050 --> 02:06:50.210
I'm gonna take your family apart
piece by piece. You understand me?

1042
02:06:50.320 --> 02:06:52.380
Piece by piece. Shut up!

1043
02:06:53.590 --> 02:06:56.380
<i>I don't want your money!</i>

1044
02:06:56.490 --> 02:07:00.120
Do you understand me?
You understand me? I want you.

1045
02:07:33.260 --> 02:07:35.350
I'm listening.

1046
02:07:36.800 --> 02:07:40.160
<i>I'm listening. Daniel. I'm listening.</i>

1047
02:07:46.370 --> 02:07:49.670
<i>All right.
I will give you a life for a life.</i>

1048
02:07:51.280 --> 02:07:53.840
Whose life?
What are you talking about?

1049
02:07:53.950 --> 02:07:56.710
<i>Whose life. Daniel? I want you.</i>

1050
02:07:56.820 --> 02:08:00.310
I will give you her life for your life.

1051
02:08:00.420 --> 02:08:04.880
And in exchange.
I will get my life back.

1052
02:08:04.990 --> 02:08:08.980
- What life? Whose life?
- The girl's. Pita's.

1053
02:08:12.900 --> 02:08:17.060
- Pita's dead.
- Creasy!

1054
02:08:17.170 --> 02:08:22.510
<i>I'm a businessman.
A girl dead is worth nothing. She's alive.</i>

1055
02:08:26.810 --> 02:08:28.780
All right.

1056
02:08:30.720 --> 02:08:32.910
I want proof of life. You hear me?

1057
02:08:33.020 --> 02:08:35.990
I want proof of life.
I want... I want...

1058
02:08:36.090 --> 02:08:38.520
I want the name of her bear.
What does she call her bear?

1059
02:08:38.620 --> 02:08:41.250
<i>You tell her to tell you...</i>

1060
02:08:41.360 --> 02:08:44.890
to tell me what she calls her bear.

1061
02:09:13.690 --> 02:09:16.290
- Yeah?
- Creasy.

1062
02:09:16.400 --> 02:09:19.390
<i>She calls the bear Creasy Bear.</i>

1063
02:09:35.310 --> 02:09:37.280
Okay.

1064
02:09:39.120 --> 02:09:41.710
O- Okay.

1065
02:09:41.820 --> 02:09:44.380
I give you your brother.
you give me the girl.

1066
02:09:46.130 --> 02:09:48.460
- All right.
- Where?

1067
02:10:32.140 --> 02:10:34.040
Hello?

1068
02:10:34.140 --> 02:10:36.800
Lisa. listen to me. Don't hang up.

1069
02:10:36.910 --> 02:10:39.100
I think Pita's alive.

1070
02:10:40.910 --> 02:10:43.140
I can't take this anymore.

1071
02:10:43.250 --> 02:10:45.180
Take the road to Puebla.

1072
02:10:45.280 --> 02:10:48.150
Get off junction 34. south side.

1073
02:10:48.250 --> 02:10:50.280
I'll meet you there in two hours.

1074
02:11:26.700 --> 02:11:28.600
So where is she?

1075
02:11:31.140 --> 02:11:34.270
She's right over there.
You see those two cars out there?

1076
02:11:39.580 --> 02:11:42.850
Pita's kidnapper. Daniel...

1077
02:11:42.950 --> 02:11:46.280
this is his brother.

1078
02:11:47.660 --> 02:11:49.780
Here.

1079
02:11:49.890 --> 02:11:53.620
I'm goin' up on the bridge to get Pita.

1080
02:11:53.730 --> 02:11:56.490
<i>If anything goes wrong.
you put it to his head.</i>

1081
02:11:58.070 --> 02:12:00.190
You pull the trigger. all right?

1082
02:12:01.240 --> 02:12:03.760
You understand?

1083
02:12:06.840 --> 02:12:09.210
You don't...

1084
02:12:09.310 --> 02:12:12.580
Let him loose until she's with you.

1085
02:12:12.680 --> 02:12:14.650
You got it?

1086
02:12:17.120 --> 02:12:19.780
And you don't wait for me. okay?

1087
02:12:22.520 --> 02:12:24.250
Yeah.

1088
02:12:24.360 --> 02:12:27.920
- You'll be all right. You okay?
- Yeah.

1089
02:14:13.100 --> 02:14:15.000
Creasy!

1090
02:14:16.770 --> 02:14:18.740
Creasy!

1091
02:14:19.910 --> 02:14:22.380
Creasy!

1092
02:14:38.660 --> 02:14:41.060
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1093
02:14:41.160 --> 02:14:43.860
They didn't hurt you?

1094
02:14:43.960 --> 02:14:46.300
Hi.

1095
02:14:49.040 --> 02:14:53.340
Your mother's waitin' for you. She's right
down there at the end of the bridge.

1096
02:14:53.440 --> 02:14:57.070
- Okay? You go home.
- Okay.

1097
02:14:57.180 --> 02:14:59.910
- All right.
- Where are you goin'?

1098
02:15:03.780 --> 02:15:06.250
I'm goin' home too.

1099
02:15:07.290 --> 02:15:09.190
I'm goin' to Blue Bayou.

1100
02:15:13.460 --> 02:15:16.090
Oh. Hey.

1101
02:15:16.200 --> 02:15:19.530
I got something for you.

1102
02:15:21.600 --> 02:15:23.590
I got the last number too.

1103
02:15:23.700 --> 02:15:26.540
I love you. Creasy.

1104
02:15:29.040 --> 02:15:31.710
And you love me. don't you?

1105
02:15:32.810 --> 02:15:34.910
Yes. I do.

1106
02:15:35.020 --> 02:15:38.210
With all my heart. Pita. go.

1107
02:15:38.320 --> 02:15:40.290
